        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(openai-completions): relocate dynamic cache-boundary suffix for implicit prefix-cache providers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #94518. Builds on the approach in #94945, rebased onto current main.\n\n### The problem\nThe system prompt contains a `<!-- OPENCLAW_CACHE_BOUNDARY -->` marker separating stable content (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, tool descriptions) from per-turn-volatile content (Runtime block, active exec sessions).\n\nFor providers with **explicit prompt caching** (Anthropic), the boundary is used with `cache_control` breakpoints — only the stable prefix gets cached, and the dynamic suffix is sent normally.\n\nFor providers with **implicit prefix caching** (DeepSeek, and potentially other OpenAI-compatible providers), the cache is based on literal request prefix matching. Any change in the leading system message invalidates the cache for the entire conversation that follows. Since the Runtime block changes every turn, this destroys cache effectiveness.\n\nReported impact on DeepSeek: cache hit rate dropped from ~95% to <10% after the 6.x upgrade, increasing per-call costs ~10x.\n\n### The fix\nWhen `preserveSystemPromptCacheBoundary` is `false` (default for non-Anthropic providers), split the system prompt at the boundary marker and relocate the dynamic suffix to a **trailing system message**. The stable prefix stays as a byte-identical leading message, keeping the implicit prefix cache valid across turns.\n\n### What differs from #94945\n- Rebased onto current main (openai-completions.ts restructured — imports, type exports, and function organization changed significantly)\n- Removes unused `cache-retention.js` import that no longer exists in current main\n- Does not include the original PR's test changes (test file structure changed)\n\n### Known limitation\nNo live API validation has been performed against providers that may reject system messages appearing after user turns. OpenAI's API accepts this; other OpenAI-compatible providers should be tested.\n\n### Impact assessment for providers with `cacheRead`/`cacheWrite` costs configured\nIf a provider reports cache pricing and uses implicit prefix caching, this fix directly reduces per-call cost. If they don't use implicit caching, the change is harmless (one extra trailing system message).\n\n**Test plan:** Manual validation against target provider. Unit tests should verify:\n1. Stable prefix is sent as first message\n2. Dynamic suffix is sent as trailing message after user/assistant history\n3. `preserveSystemPromptCacheBoundary: true` (Anthropic path) is unchanged",
